---
import ServicePage from '../../components/ServicePage.astro';

const orgId = new URL('/#organization', Astro.site).href;
const schema = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'Service',
    name: 'Music Business Management',
    serviceType: 'Entertainment business management',
    description:
      'Day-to-day financial management for musicians and creatives: money management, income and expense tracking, bill pay, cash flow, and coordination of the whole business team.',
    provider: { '@id': orgId },
    areaServed: [
      { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'Nashville Metropolitan Area' },
      { '@type': 'Country', name: 'United States' },
    ],
  },
];
---

<ServicePage
  title="Music Business Management for Artists & Bands | BriBiz"
  description="What an entertainment business manager actually does: day-to-day money management, cash flow, bill pay, and keeping your whole business team on the same page."
  breadcrumbName="Business Management"
  heroTitle="Music Business Management"
  schema={schema}
  related={[
    ['Tour accounting', '/services/tour-management/'],
    ['Royalty accounting', '/services/royalty-accounting/'],
    ['Tax services', '/services/tax-services/'],
  ]}
>
  <p>
    "What do you even do?" It's the question we hear most, usually from an artist
    sitting in our office for the first time. Fair enough. Growing a business in
    the music industry means combining the rigors of artistry with the stress of
    entrepreneurship – and somewhere between writing, recording, and touring,
    somebody has to run the business.
  </p>
  <p>
    That's us. You make your music. We make sure the business underneath it
    actually works.
  </p>

  <h2>The Day-to-Day</h2>
  <p>
    Think about the loops running in the back of your brain late at night.
    <em>Did I pay that bill yet? Should I be filing my quarterlies? Who owes me
    money? Did I miss a royalty check?</em> Our job is to let you turn those
    loops off. On a day-to-day basis, your business manager will:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Manage your money and maintain healthy cash flow</li>
    <li>Track income and expenses, and reconcile the accounts</li>
    <li>Collect every payment owed to you</li>
    <li>Pay every bill on time</li>
    <li>Deal with vendors and keep financial communication flowing</li>
    <li>Keep you up to speed with regular reports</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The detail-work is where we shine. For some clients we've overseen the sale
    of a publishing catalog; for others we've <a
    href="/services/royalty-accounting/">tracked royalties and chased down
    discrepancies</a> in payments. The goal is always the same: a music business
    that runs, with money flowing the way it should.
  </p>

  <h2>The Center of the Wheel</h2>
  <p>
    We often describe ourselves as the hub of a wheel. Your CPA, your insurance
    agent, your royalty agent, your financial adviser – how often do they all sit
    in the same room and have a productive conversation about you and your goals?
    The answer is never. We exist to be that conversation.
  </p>
  <p>
    And unlike firms that keep everything in-house, we prefer to stay free
    agents, hiring the best for each client. Why limit ourselves to one tax
    accountant when one client is planning for retirement, one has to account for
    global earnings, and one runs a nonprofit? Need a CPA? We know someone. A new
    insurance provider? We know someone for that, too – and we'll sit in the
    meetings with you to make sure it's a good fit.
  </p>

  <h2>Business Manager, Artist Manager, Bookkeeper – Who Does What?</h2>
  <p>
    You likely need both a business manager and an artist manager; many artist
    managers won't work with an artist who doesn't have one. In corporate terms:
    you're the Owner. Your artist manager works like a COO, creating
    opportunities – tours, sponsorships, partnerships. Your business manager is
    the CFO, managing the money and the details so you never stall.
  </p>
  <p>
    A bookkeeper, on the other hand, is almost entirely reactive – recording and
    settling transactions after you've already made the decisions. A business
    manager is proactive: we catch everything that's happened, assess what's
    happening now, and plan for what's coming.
  </p>
  <p>
    One thing we won't do: manage your career or make creative decisions. We're
    here to organize your business, maximize your financial health, and give you
    the peace of mind to focus on what you do best. The creative calls are yours.
  </p>
</ServicePage>
